<h1>CME Calendar</h1><br><P>
</center>

<b>
For information on programs not listed in this month's "Coming Events," call (800) 621-1773, Ext 5872, or (312) 280-5872, or write to John Sprovieri, managing editor,  The DO , American Osteopathic Association, 142 E Ontario St, Chicago, IL 60611-2864.<BR><p>

<BR>
<Font color="#ff0000"><H2>Continuing programs</Font></H2>
<BR>
  Sutherland techniques. <BR>
Tri-City Health Centre, Osteopathic Manipulation Techniques (with emphasis on Sutherland Techniques), Dallas. CME credit: Category 1-A, 3 hrs anticipated per lecture. Contact Conrad A. Speece, DO, 10622 Garland Rd, Dallas, TX 75218 (214) 321-2673. Courses held the first Wednesday of each month.<BR>
<BR>

<BR>
<Font color="#ff0000"><H2>January<BR></Font></H2>
<BR>
Jan 18-22--Craniosacral technique.<BR>
Michigan State University College of Osteopathic Medicine, Craniosacral Technique: Level I, Windmill Inn, Tucson, Ariz. CME credit: Category 1-A, 40 hrs anticipated. Contact Betty Wilson, dir of CME, MSU-COM, A306 East Fee Hall, East Lansing, MI 48824-1316 (800) 437-0001 or (517) 353-9714. Registration: $1,000; physicians in training, $750. Prerequisite: MSU-COM's Principles of Manual Medicine.<BR>
<BR>
Jan 23-24--Surgeons.<BR>
American College of Osteopathic Surgeons, Breast Cancer Today--A Review, Orlando, Fla. CME credit: Category 1-A, 12 hrs anticipated. Contact ACOS, 123 N Henry St, Alexandria, VA 22134-2903 (800) 888-1312 or (703) 684-0416.<BR>
<BR>
Jan 23-25--Emergency medicine.<BR>
West Virginia School of Osteopathic Medicine, emergency medicine seminar, Canaan Valley Ski Resort, Davis, W Va. CME credit: Category 1-A, 15 hrs anticipated. Contact Barbara B. Elliott, CME coordinator, WVSOM, 400 N Lee St, Lewisburg, WV 24901 (304) 647-6257.<BR>
<BR>
Jan 23-26--Florida's Pinellas County. <BR>
Pinellas County (Fla) Osteopathic Medical Society, 8th annual winter conference, Doubletree Surfside Resort, Clearwater Beach, Fla. CME credit: Category 1-A, 28 hrs anticipated. Contact Kenneth E. Webster, PhD, exec dir, PCOMS, 7800 66th St, N, Suite 102, Pinellas Park, FL 34665 (813) 545-3627.<BR>
<BR>
 Jan 23-26--Michigan FPs. <BR>
Michigan Association of Osteopathic Family Physicians, An Update in Family Practice Medicine, Sugar Loaf Ski Resort, Cedar, Mich. CME credit: Category 1-A, 25 hrs anticipated. Contact Melinda Hendrix, admin asst, MAOFP, 2445 Woodlake Circle, Okemos, MI 48864 (800) 657-1556 or (517) 347-1555.<BR>
<BR>
 Jan 23-26--Missouri FPs. <BR>
Missouri Society of the American College of Osteopathic Family Physicians, annual conference, Adam's Mark Hotel, Kansas City, Mo. CME credit: Category 1-A, 33 hrs anticipated. Contact Judy Thompson, meeting coordinator, Missouri Society of the ACOFP, PO Box 748, Jefferson City, MO 65102 (573) 634-3415.<BR>
<BR>
 Jan 23-26--Oregon's winter. <BR>
Osteopathic Physicians and Surgeons of Oregon, annual winter convention, Riverhouse Hotel, Bend, Ore. Contact Jeff Heatherington, exec dir, OPSO, 2121 SW Broadway, Suite 120, Portland, OR 97201 (503) 222-2779.<BR>
<BR>
 Jan 24-25--PCOM Founders Day. <BR>
Philadelphia College of Osteopathic Medicine, Founders Day and class reunions. CME credit: Category 1-A, 8 hrs anticipated. Contact Linda Miller, CME coordinator, PCOM, 4170 City Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19131-1694 (215) 871-6348. Registration: free.<BR>
<BR>
 Jan 26-Feb 2--CME in St Thomas. <BR>
Philadelphia College of Osteopathic Medicine, 13th annual post-Founders Day seminar, Sapphire Beach Resort, St Thomas, US Virgin Islands. CME credit: Category 1-A, 40 hrs anticipated. Contact Hale T. Pefall, exec dir of alumni relations, PCOM, 4180 City Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19131-1694 (215) 871-6148. Registration: $595.<BR>
<BR>
 Jan 31-Feb 2--New Hampshire. <BR>
New Hampshire Osteopathic Association, annual ski and CME conference, Loon Mountain, Lincoln, NH. CME credit: Category 1-A, 12 hrs anticipated. Contact the Northeastern Small States Consortium, 100 Concord St, Framingham, MA 01701 (800) 982-7247 or (508) 872-8900.<BR>
<BR>
 Jan 31-Feb 2--Oklahoma's winter. <BR>
Oklahoma Osteopathic Association, annual winter seminar, Healthcare Issues for the Elderly, Women, Adolescents and Children, Adam's Mark Hotel, Tulsa, Okla. CME credit: Category 1-A, 17 hrs anticipated. Contact Bob E. Jones, exec dir, OOA, 4848 N Lincoln Blvd, Oklahoma City, OK 73105-3321 (800) 522-8379 (within Oklahoma) or (405) 528-4848.<BR>
