<Font color="#ff0000"><H2>  October 1998<BR></Font></H2>
<BR>
  Oct 6-10, 1998--AOA convention. <BR>
American Osteopathic Association, 103rd Annual Convention and Scientific Seminar, New Orleans Convention Center. CME credit: Category 1-A, 26 hrs anticipated, plus 3 hrs for visiting the commercial exhibits, 1 hr for visiting the scientific exhibits, 3 hrs for attending the conventionwide AIDS seminar, 3 hrs for attending the conventionwide managed care seminar, 2.5 hrs for attending the conventionwide risk management seminar, and 1 hr for each conventionwide breakfast seminar. Contact Ann M. Wittner, dir of admin, AOA, 142 E Ontario St, Chicago, IL 60611-2864 (800) 621-1773, Ext 5, or (312) 280-7433.<BR>
 About the program <BR>
The 1998 convention will include the AOA Research Conference and the meetings of the following groups: American Academy of Osteopathy, American Osteopathic Academy of Addiction Medicine, American Osteopathic College of Allergy and Immunology, American Osteopathic College of Dermatology, American College of Osteopathic Emergency Physicians, American College of Osteopathic Family Physicians, American College of Osteopathic Neurologists and Psychiatrists, American Osteopathic College of Occupational and Preventive Medicine, American College of Osteopathic Pain Management and Sclerotherapy, American Osteopathic College of Pathologists, American Osteopathic College of Rehabilitation Medicine, American Osteopathic College of Rheumatology, American Osteopathic Academy of Sports Medicine, and Auxiliary to the AOA.<BR>
<BR>
 Oct 7-11, 1998--New Mexico's fall. <BR>
New Mexico Osteopathic Medical Association, 18th annual Balloon Fiesta Medical Symposium, Holiday Inn Pyramid, Albuquerque, NM. Contact Floyd F. Smith, exec dir, NMOMA, PO Box 90396, Albuquerque, NM 87199-0396 (505) 828-1905.<BR>
<BR>
 Oct 14-18, 1998--Radiologists. <BR>
American Osteopathic College of Radiology, annual convention, The Westin La Paloma, Tucson, Ariz. Contact Pamela A. Smith, exec dir, AOCR, 119 E Second St, Milan, MO 63556 (816) 265-4011.<BR>
<BR>
 Oct 16-18, 1998--Vermont. <BR>
Vermont State Association of Osteopathic Physicians and Surgeons, annual Fall Foliage Convention, Radisson Hotel, Burlington, Vt. Contact the Northeastern Small States Consortium, 100 Concord St, Framingham, MA 01701 (800) 982-7247 or (508) 872-8900, or contact John M. Peterson, DO, exec dir, VSAOPS, 72 Barre St, Montpelier, VT 05602 (802) 229-9418.<BR>
<BR>
