<HEAD>
<TITLE>(AOA / CME Examinations)</TITLE>

<META name="description" content="American Osteopathic Association.">
<META name="keywords" content="Osteopathic, DO, Doctor of Osteopathy, 
Health, Continuing Medical Education, CME, CME Boards, Examinations">


</HEAD>


<BODY background="../../bkgd.gif"
      BGCOLOR="#7093db"
      text="#000000"
      link="#ff0000"
      vlink="#00009c"
      alink="#ffffff">

<Center>


<IMG SRC="cevents.gif" HEIGHT=155 WIDTH=433><P>


<img src="../../rule2.gif">


<H1>CME Board Examinations</H1>
</center>

<BR>
<B>   April 3--Neurology and psychiatry.</B> <BR>
American Osteopathic Board of Neurology and Psychiatry, part I: written examination, Wyndham Emerald Plaza Hotel, San Diego. Contact AOBNP, 2250 Chapel Ave, W, Suite 100, Cherry Hill, NJ 08002-2000 (609) 667-5717. Deadline: Feb 12.<BR>
<BR>
<B> April 5--Surgery. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Surgery, written examinations, Rosemont (Ill) Center. Contact Sharon D. Alexiades, corresponding secretary, AOBS, 3 MacKoil Ave, Dayton, OH 45403 (937) 252-0868. Deadline: March 31.<BR>
<BR>
<B> April 6--Rehabilitation medicine. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Rehabilitation Medicine, part I written examination, Philadelphia. Contact Julie Ataee, exec assistant, AOBRM, 2214 Elmira Ave, Des Plaines, IL 60018 (847) 699-0048. Deadline: Feb 15.<BR>
<BR>
<B> April 12--Occupational medicine--added qualifications. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Preventive Medicine, examination for certificate of added qualifications in occupational medicine, The Ritz Carlton--Atlanta. Contact Capt George E. Hill, DO, MPH, MC, USN (Ret), secretary-treasurer, AOBPM, 411 Stoneridge Court, Grand Junction, CO 81053 (970) 245-4533. Deadline: March 1. 
<BR>
Note: To be eligible to take the exam, a DO must have received primary board certification from at least one AOA certifying board and must have completed all three parts of the American Osteopathic College of Occupational and Preventive Medicine's Basic Course in Occupational and Environmental Medicine.<BR>
<BR>
<B> April 12--Preventive medicine. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Preventive Medicine, written and oral examinations, The Ritz Carlton--Atlanta. Contact Capt George E. Hill, DO, MPH, MC, USN (Ret), secretary-treasurer, AOBPM, 411 Stoneridge Court, Grand Junction, CO 81053 (970) 245-4533. Deadline: March 1. Note: In addition to being examined in the specialty of preventive medicine, each candidate will be examined in one of the following subspecialties: aerospace medicine, occupational and environmental medicine, and public health.<BR>
<BR>
<B> May 3-4--Obstetrics and gynecology. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology, objective and clinical examinations, Chicago. Contact Joseph P. Bonanno, DO, secretary-treasurer, AOBOG, 5200 S Ellis Ave, Chicago, IL 60615 (312) 947-4630. Deadlines: objective examination, March 1; clinical examination, April 1.<BR>
<BR>
<B> May 6--Ophthalmology and otolaryngology. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Boards of Ophthalmology and Otolaryngology--Head and Neck Surgery, oral examinations, Loews Ventana Canyon Resort, Tucson, Ariz. Contact Sharon D. Alexiades, corresponding secretary, AOBOO--HNS, 3 MacKoil Ave, Dayton, OH 45403 (937) 252-0868. Deadline: Jan 31.<BR>
<BR>
<B> May 7--Ophthalmology and otolaryngology. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Boards of Ophthalmology and Otolaryngology--Head and Neck Surgery, written examinations, Loews Ventana Canyon Resort, Tucson, Ariz. Contact Sharon D. Alexiades, corresponding secretary, AOBOO--HNS, 3 MacKoil Ave, Dayton, OH 45403 (937) 252-0868. Deadline: March 31.<BR>
<BR>
<B> May 17--Neurology. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Neurology and Psychiatry, part II: clinical and oral examinations in neurology, Michigan Institute of Neurological Disorders, Detroit. Contact AOBNP, 2250 Chapel Ave, W, Suite 100, Cherry Hill, NJ 08002-2000 (609) 667-5717. Deadline: March 19.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Sept 20--Anesthesiology. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Anesthesiology, oral examination, The Breakers, Palm Beach, Fla. Contact Diann Hubbard, corresponding secretary, AOBA, 17201 E US Highway 40, Independence, MO 64055-6427 (816) 373-4700. Deadline: April 1.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 18-19--Family medicine. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Family Physicians, examination, San Antonio. Contact Carol Thoma, exec dir, AOBFP, 330 E Algonquin Rd, Suite 6, Arlington Heights, IL 60005 (847) 640-8477. Deadline: July 1.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 18-19--Obstetrics and gynecology. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology, clinical examination, Chicago. Contact Joseph P. Bonanno, DO, secretary-treasurer, AOBOG, 5200 S Ellis Ave, Chicago, IL 60615 (312) 947-4630. Deadline: Sept 1.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 19--Addiction medicine. <BR></B>
Conjoint board examination for certificate of added qualifications in addiction medicine, San Antonio. The exam is being offered by a conjoint board composed of the American Osteopathic Board of Anesthesiology, the American Osteopathic Board of Family Physicians, the American Osteopathic Board of Internal Medicine, the American Osteopathic Board of Neurology and Psychiatry, and the American Osteopathic Academy of Addiction Medicine. For more information, contact any of the conjoint board's member organizations. Deadline: July 1. Note: To be eligible to take the exam, a DO must have obtained primary board certification from at least one of the certifying boards conducting the exam.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 19--Dermatology. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Dermatology, examinations, San Antonio. Contact Thomas H. Bonino, DO, secretary-treasurer, AOBD, 25510 Plymouth Rd, Redford, MI 48239 (313) 937-1200. Deadline: April 1.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 19--Family medicine--geriatrics. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Family Physicians, examination for certificate of added qualifications in geriatric medicine, San Antonio. Contact Carol Thoma, exec dir, AOBFP, 330 E Algonquin Rd, Suite 6, Arlington Heights, IL 60005 (847) 640-8477. Deadline: July 1.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 19--Family medicine--recertification. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Family Physicians, recertification examination, San Antonio. Contact Carol Thoma, exec dir, AOBFP, 330 E Algonquin Rd, Suite 6, Arlington Heights, IL 60005 (847) 640-8477. Deadline: July 1.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 19--Rehabilitation medicine. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Rehabilitation Medicine, part I written examination and part II oral examination, San Antonio. Contact Julie Ataee, exec assistant, AOBRM, 2214 Elmira Ave, Des Plaines, IL 60018 (847) 699-0048. Deadline: April 15.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 19--Sports medicine. <BR></B>
Conjoint board examination for certificate of added qualifications in sports medicine, San Antonio. The exam is being offered by a conjoint board composed of the American Osteopathic Board of Emergency Medicine, the American Osteopathic Board of Family Physicians, the American Osteopathic Board of Internal Medicine, the American Osteopathic Board of Pediatrics, the American Osteopathic Board of Preventive Medicine, the American Osteopathic Board of Rehabilitation Medicine, and the American Osteopathic Academy of Sports Medicine. For more information, contact any of the conjoint board's member organizations. Deadline: July 1. Note: To be eligible to take the exam, a DO must have obtained primary board certification from at least one of the certifying boards conducting the exam.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Oct 22--Occupational medicine--added qualifications. <BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Preventive Medicine, examination for certificate of added qualifications in occupational medicine, San Antonio. Contact Capt George E. Hill, DO, MPH, MC, USN (Ret), secretary-treasurer, AOBPM, 411 Stoneridge Court, Grand Junction, CO 81053 (970) 245-4533. Deadline: Sept 1. Note: To be eligible to take the exam, a DO must have received primary board certification from at least one AOA certifying board and must have completed all three parts of the American Osteopathic College of Occupational and Preventive Medicine's Basic Course in Occupational and Environmental Medicine.<BR>
<BR>
<B> Nov 27-28--OMM.<BR></B>
American Osteopathic Board of Special Proficiency in Osteopathic Manipulative Medicine, written, oral and practical examinations, Indianapolis. Contact Stephen J. Noone, exec dir, AOBSPOMM, 3500 DePauw Blvd, Suite 1080, Indianapolis, IN 46268-1136 (317) 879-1881. Deadline: May 27.<BR>
<BR>

Back to the <A HREF="cmeidx.htm">CME Index Page.</A>
