<head>

<title>Photosynthesis</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>
<a href="gifs/photo.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_photo.gif"></a>
<br>
<h2>Photosynthesis</h2>
<h4>Hybrid Windows/Mac #34465</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr>
<a href="gifs/photo1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_photo1.gif"></a>

<i>Photosynthesis</i>: Some of the topics covered in this program are: the roles of carbon dioxide,
water, oxygen, glucose, and light energy; waves, wavelengths, and the visible light
spectrum; photons, pigments including chlorophyll b and the carotenoids; chloroplasts; the
chemical reaction for photosynthesis; light reactions including detailed examination of
photosystems I and II, electron transport chains, and the generation of ATP and NADPH;
dark reactions; and the Calvin Cycle.
<br clear=right>
