<HEAD>
<TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><P>

<center><P>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br><img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><br><P>
</center><P>
<a href="gifs/microcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_microcv.gif"></a><P>
<BR><P>

<h2>Microscopic Anatomy CD-ROM</h2>
<h4>Windows/Macintosh CD-ROM #35859</h4><BR>
<BR clear=left>
<HR><P>

<a href="gifs/micro2.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=20 src="smgifs/s_micro2.gif"></a><P>

Microscopic Anatomy is an interactive cellular anatomy tutorial modeled after classroom exercises.  Its extensive testing and review capabilities facilitate students  comprehension of this basic science curriculum.  The CD presents a logical organization of 1,200 histologic slides and electron micrographs, each with references to degrees of magnification, detailed explanatory text, descriptions of the staining procedures for the various specimens, and color arrows highlighting key structures.  
<BR clear=right>

<a href="gifs/micro1.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=20 src="smgifs/s_micro1.gif"></a><P>

This CD-ROM also features a five minute video demonstrating the set-up and use of a microscope.  Microscopic Anatomy also includes extensive quizzing and review features.  The interactive  practical  and written exam formats draw on a bank of more than 1,750 questions which offer immediate feedback and reinforcement.<BR>
<BR clear=left>

Features:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Over 1,200 digitized histologic slides and electron micrographs<BR>
<LI>References to degrees of magnification represented in slides<BR>
<LI>Zoom capabilities<BR>
<LI>Enlarge slide to full screen<BR>
<LI>Electronic quizzing<BR>
<LI>1,750 multiple choice questions<BR>
</UL>

