<TITLE>Radiologic Anatomy</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><P>
<BR>
<BR>
<center><P>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br><img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><br><P>
</center><P>
<a href="gifs/radiocv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_radiocv.gif"></a><P>
<BR><P>

<h2>Radiologic Anatomy CD-ROM</h2><BR>
<h4>Windows/Macintosh CD-ROM #35860</h4><BR>
<BR clear=left>
<HR><P>

<a href="gifs/radio1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=15 src="smgifs/s_radio1.gif"></a><P>

Radiologic Anatomy is an unparalleled presentation of the fundamentals of normal anatomy as seen on modern diagnostic images.  You will find this CD to be an invaluable teaching aid, as it provides views of the human body as students are most likely to see in clinical practice.  The program focuses on normal anatomy, but also includes introductory radiologic pathology, laboratory dissection photos for gross anatomic correlations, and radiologic technique video clips which demonstrate methods for obtaining various radiographs.<BR>
<BR clear=right>

<a href="gifs/radio2.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=7 src="smgifs/s_radio2.gif"></a><P>

Imaging Modalities: <BR>
Plain Films, CT Scans, MRI Scans, Fluoroscopy, Angiography, Barium Studies, Cholangiography, Ureterography, Intravenous Pyelography, Hysterosalpingography<BR>
<BR clear=left>

<a href="gifs/radio3.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_radio3.gif"></a><P>

Contents: Skull and Spine / Head and Neck / Tissues / Chest and Abdominal Walls / Lungs and Pleura / Heart and Great Vessels / Mediastinum / Gastrointestinal and Genitourinary Systems / Retroperitoneum / Upper and Lower Extremities / Anatomic, Clinical and Technique Correlations<BR>
<BR clear=right>

