<html>
<head>

<title>Redox</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/redox.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_redox.gif"></a>
<BR>
<h2>Redox Videodisc</h2>

<h4>Videodisc #20678</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><i>Redox</i> reactions are among the most important and universal in chemistry. Redox, an
interactive videodisc, allows these extremely dangerous, traditionally expensive and
hard-to-demonstrate chemistry experiments to be safely reviewed as often as needed. 
Through the power of this videodisc, these experiments can be viewed and reviewed until
they have been mastered.  <P>
The videodisc provides students with images of reactions and laboratory equipments that are
not usually available for hands-on experiments.  <P>

The two-sided disc contains 57 experiments.  Among them are: Reaction of Hydrogen and
Chlorine Initiated by Light, Preparation of Oxygen from Mercury (II) Oxide, Ammonia
Oxidation Catalyzed by Platinum, Peroxyacetone Decomposition, Electroplating Chromium,
Vanadium Oxidation States, and Redox Potentials.  <P>

Included with this package is a barcode manual and descriptive listing of all experiments
included on the disc.  A computer     segment also is packaged with the product.

<br clear=left>
<hr>

