<HEAD>
<TITLE>Origins of the Constitution</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><P>

<center><P>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br><img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><br><P>
</center><P>
<a href="gifs/constcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_constcv.gif"></a><P>
<BR><P>

<BR>
<H2>Origins of the Constitution CD-ROM</H2><BR>
<H4>Windows CD-ROM #35880</H4><P>
<H4>Macintosh CD-ROM  #35881</H4><BR>
<BR clear=left>
<HR><P>

<a href="gifs/const1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_const1.gif"></a><P>

This interactive multimedia tutorial enables students to explore the establishment of the United States government.  Students see how personalities, philosophies, and political realities contributed to the making of the Constitution.  Visuals and narration are highlighted by quotations and thoughts from people of the time.
<BR clear=right> 

<a href="gifs/const2.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_const2.gif"></a><P>

The program analyzes the political events of the Revolution and the change from the Articles of Confederation to the Constitution, and recounts the process of ratification and the inclusion of the Bill of Rights.  Text files include the Articles of Confederation, the Constitution, the Declaration of Independence, Federalist Papers, and the Declaration of Rights.<BR>
<BR clear=left>

