<title>Dynamic Human</title>



</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">



<center>

<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br><img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><br>

</center>

<a href="gifs/dynamcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_dynamcv.gif"></a>

<BR>

<h2>Dynamic Human CD-ROM</h2>



<h4>Windows CD-ROM #34173</h4>

<h4>Macintosh  CD-ROM #29017</h4>

<BR clear=left>
<hr>
<a href="gifs/dynam3.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_dynam3.gif"></a>

Wm. C. Brown Publishers presents the next step in the study of anatomy and physiology.  <I>The Dynamic Human </I>  CD-ROM interactively  illustrates the complex relationships between anatomical structures and their functions in the human body.  Realistic, three-dimensional visuals are the premiere feature of this exciting learning tool.<P>

 <a href="gifs/dynam6.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_dynam6.gif"></a>

These visuals elaborate the difficult concepts of functional anatomy.  After a brief introduction, this interactive program covers homeostasis and each body system, always demonstrating to the   viewer the interactions between the systems. Outstanding three-dimensional viewing capabilities are completely controlled by you.  Just click the arrow keys on your keyboard or screen to rotate major organs in any direction, zoom in for a closer look, or hold a specific position for closer study.<P>

<br clear=left>



