<head>

<title>Explorations in Health & Psychology</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/healthcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_healthcv.gif"></a>
<BR>
<h2>Explorations in Health & Psychology CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #29255</h4>
<h4>Macintosh CD-ROM #29255</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/health1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_health1.gif"></a>
<I>Explorations in Health & Psychology</I> allows your students to actively investigate vital
processes as they should be explored with movement, color, sound, and interaction. Your
students will learn about the physical basis of drug addiction at the synaptic level by
exploring how cocaine directly affects a nerve.  This simulation lets the student vary the
amount and frequency of cocaine used and examine how patterns of drug use impact
addiction.
<a href="gifs/health2.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_health2.gif"></a><P>
<I>Explorations</I> also features a module that enables the teacher or student to select activity levels
for the day, enter the foods to be eaten at each meal, then see the calories and total grams of
carbohydrates, proteins, and fats tallied.  Usage of this module determines how weight is
gained or lost by altering diet and activity patterns.

<br clear=left>
