<h2>Enzymes</h2>
<h4>Hybrid Windows/Mac #34460</h4>
<br clear=left>
<hr>
<a href="gifs/enzymain.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_enzymain.gif"></a>
<i>Enzymes</i>: The biological importance of enzymes becomes apparent as this    program vividly
reveals how enzymes work to sustain life.  This program      examines: functions of enzymes
in living cells; chemical reaction; catalyst; substrates; energy of activation; enzyme structure
including amino acid chains, active site, and relative size of an enzyme; the lock-and-key
model and the induced fit model; enzyme activity; factors affecting enzyme activity including
temperature, pH, enzyme concentration, substrate concentration, cofactors, competitive
inhibitors, and noncompetitive inhibitors.

