<title>Investigating Plant Science</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/plantcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_plantcv.gif"></a>

<h2>Investigating Plant Science CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #34167</h4>
<h4>(Windows Only)</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/plant1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_plant1.gif"></a>
<BR>
<i>Investigating Plant Science</i> provides students with a multimedia tool to study plants and the
way they respond to the environment, interact with animals, grow and develop.  The
program consists of a colorful range of text, images and student assignments.  The features
include: Reference, which allows for brief abstracts of articles relating to plant science
topics; Studies, which includes information about plants that are suitable for classroom use,
summaries of school      projects and tips for techniques in plant investigations; Glossary, a
list of technical terms; and Flora, which contains images to help in identification of plants.

<a href="gifs/plant6.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_plant6.gif"></a><P>

This CD-ROM will enable students, through interaction with the resource, to become more
independent investigators.

