<title>Doing Chemistry</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/doingche.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_doingche.gif"></a>
<BR>
<h2>Doing Chemistry Videodisc</h2>

<h4>Videodisc #20679</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr>This critically acclaimed image database contains 136 experiments and demonstrations in
three discs.  It can be used as a pre-lab demonstration of      equipment set-up, laboratory
techniques and safety precautions.  It also may be used as a substitute for lab exercises for
which time or equipment is not available.  <P>

The package consists of three, two-sided laserdiscs, a hypercard stack, and more than 500
pages of accompanying print material broken down into three categories: teacher-performed
experiments, student-performed experiments, and those       suitable for either mode.
<H3>Contents</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Measurement
<LI>Stoichiometry
<LI>Atomic Structure
<LI>Bonding
<LI>Reactions
<LI>Solutions
<LI>Gases & Phases
<LI>Thermochemistry
<LI>Acid & Base
<LI>Equilibrium & Kenetics
<LI>Electrochemistry
<LI>Computer Applications
</UL>
