<a href="gifs/a&pvdcv1.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_a&pvdcv1.gif"></a>
<BR>
<h2>Anatomy & Physiology Videodisc</h2>

<h4>Videodisc #27716</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr>Now you can spark interest and encourage inquiry in your classroom with the Wm C. Brown
Publishers <i>Anatomy & Physiology Videodisc</i>. This disc allows students to investigate the
human body through    colorful animation and illustration. From digestion to protein
synthesis, this valuable teaching and learning tool is sure to get students actively involved in
their study of anatomy and physiology.
This captivating videodisc offers a complete review of the human body with over 30
animations, more than 300 illustrations, and over 150 histology, clinical and dissection
slides.  Organized around a standard approach to the study of the human body, the Wm. C.
Brown Publishers <i>Anatomy and Physiology Videodisc</i> will be the perfect complement to your
classroom and laboratory. An extensive index of all the illustrations, slides, and animations
can be found in the accompanying laser barcode directory.  The directory
provides a complete index, legend, and barcode for each image and       animation.<P>

The table of contents consists of 26 chapters including: Cell Structure and Genetic
Regulation, Skeletal System: Bone Tissue and Development, Circulatory System: Cardiac
Output and Blood Flow, and Digestive System.
