<head>

<title>Introduction to Classical Music</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/classicv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_classicv.gif"></a>

<h2>Introduction to Classical Music CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #34447</h4>
<h4>(Windows Only)</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/classic3.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_classic3.gif"></a>
<BR>
<EM>An Introduction to Classical Music</EM> provides a highly pleasurable way of exploring the world
of classical music.  The information is presented through a combination of text, pictures and
sound.  This enables the student to read about Mozart's life, see his portrait, and listen to a
selection of his work. The disc contains over 200 audio extracts, together with    information
about more than 40 composers and over 350 compositions.  
<P>
<a href="gifs/classic2.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_classic2.gif"></a><P>
Options available on this CD: <STRONG>Introduction:</STRONG> a 10-minute slide show with commentary
introducing the subject; <STRONG>Performance:</STRONG> allows you to select the type of music you want to
discover; <STRONG>Composer:</STRONG> contains 45 biographies; <STRONG>Timeline: </STRONG>relates composers to their periods in
time; and <STRONG>Index:</STRONG> gives rapid access to all of the entries on the CD.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<hr>
