<head>

<title>Exploring Ancient Cities</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/citiescv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_citiescv.gif"></a>

<h2>Exploring Ancient Cities CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #34468</h4>
<h4>Macintosh CD-ROM #34468</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/cities1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_cities1.gif"></a>
<BR>This interactive CD-ROM, produced in part with <I>Scientific American Magazine</I>, will take the
student on an exploration of four ancient civilizations.  All of the pictures, text, and movies
in this CD-ROM can be easily exported and reused for student reports.  Stories originally
appearing in <I>Scientific American</I> are brought to life with design, imagery, video, music, and
narration allowing the student to wander through each of these sites.  
<P>
<a href="gifs/cities2.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_cities2.gif"></a><P><BR>

Students can explore the sites of Crete, Petra, Pompeii, and Teotihuacan with interactive
maps, slide-shows, or narrated articles.  By examining these four cities, students will begin
to visualize what life was like during the past centuries. This is an exceptional way for
students to learn about ancient civilizations.
<br clear=left>
<hr>

