<title>U.S. History</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/ushistcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_ushist.gif"></a>
<BR>
<h2>U.S. History CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #34373</h4>
<h4>(Windows Only)</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/ushist3.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_ushist3.gif"></a>
This fascinating collection of historical multimedia recounts the story of a young republic's
gradual evolution into a world superpower; from Columbus's   discovery of the New World
through today as we embark on the twenty-first century.  <EM>Multimedia U.S. History</EM> preserves
the story of a nation for future generations through diversely selected texts, narrations,
audio-enriched animated maps, presidential biographies, photographs, still graphics, time
lines, and moving pictures.
<P>
<a href="gifs/ushist2.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_ushist2.gif"></a><P>
<BR>
Review over 15 presidential speeches from George Washington to George Bush, study
concise histories of all 50 states, follow a pictorial time line from 1492 through the present,
hear traditional American songs and period music, watch more than 15 video clips of
historical figures and events.
<br clear=left>
<hr>

