<title>Sourcebook of American History</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/amhistcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_amhist.gif"></a>
<BR>
<h2>Sourcebook of American History CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #29170</h4>
<h4>Macintosh CD-ROM #29170</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/amhist5.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_amhist5.gif"></a>
Explore the United States through the riveting writings of colonists, founders, explorers
or presidents. The <EM>CD Sourcebook of American History</EM> places nearly 20,000 pages of U.S.
history  conveniently at your fingertips. This electronic library contains nearly 1,000
primary source documents and firsthand accounts by America's important     history makers,
plus five multi-volume histories and other works by some of our country's most  eminent
historians. Scan the entire CD or search within a single book, chapter, document, or group.  
<P>

<a href="gifs/amhist7.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_amhist7.gif"></a><P>

Winner of the prestigious "Districts' Choice" award, the <EM>CD Sourcebook</EM> makes it fast, easy
and fun to find every reference to any name, date or place, issue, or event in American     
history.
<br clear=left>
