<title>A Passion for Art</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/passionc.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_passionc.gif"></a>

<h2>A Passion for Art CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #34160</h4>
<h4>Macintosh CD-ROM #34161</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/passion6.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_passion6.gif"></a>
<BR>Explore the history and beauty of one of the greatest private art collections of the early 20th
Century.  Get an inside look at the creation and acquisition of works by Renoir, Cezanne,
Matisse, and many other masters in the fabulous but seldom-seen Barnes Foundation.  Bring
post-impressionism to life with interactive documents, exquisite close-ups of the paintings,
and a tour of the Foundation. Each aspect of this work has been carefully researched and
artfully produced from its cinematic storytelling to it's graphical timeline and visual index.
<P>
<a href="gifs/passion5.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_passion5.gif"></a><P>
<BR>
View paintings full screen.  Zoom in and pan across detail, brushwork, and the artists'
signatures.  Learn about the artists and their work through accompanying text and audio
essays.
