<h2>Explorations in Cell Biology & Genetics CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #29215</h4>
<h4>Macintosh CD-ROM #29214</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/cellbio1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_cellbio1.gif"></a>
<BR>The latest in the <I>"Explorations"</I> series by Wm. C. Brown Publishers, this CD-ROM helps
students develop a better understanding of the subject matter in the process of showing these
17 relevant,        interactive animations. Students can explore vital processes with
movement, color, sound, and      interaction.
<I>Explorations</I> allows students to actively investigate concepts   related to cell biology,
metabolism and genetics. 
<a href="gifs/cellbio3.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_cellbio3.gif"></a>
For each concept explored, the user may set and reset parameters
that impact the outcome, and then evaluate those results. The CD includes: interactive color
animations, film clips and animations on related topics, and glossary with written and oral
pronunciations in English and Spanish.

