<head>

<title>Microbes in Motion</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/microbcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_microbcv.gif"></a>

<h2>Microbes in Motion CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #24596</h4>
<h4>(Windows Only)</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/microbe3.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_microbe3.gif"></a>
<BR>From classroom to resource center to your students' own personal computers, <I>Microbes in
Motion</I> brings discovery back into the education process.  Students investigate by selecting a
topic "book" from a bookcase of 16 subjects. Once selected, students explore           topics
from bacterial structure to viral structure by     simply paging through the topic books
chosen.   
The applications of this CD-ROM are only as limited as your imagination.  Expand on
module concepts and give your students the opportunity to review various segments for
self-study, exams and class discussions.  

<a href="gifs/microbe5.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_microbe5.gif"></a><p>

Other features brought to you by <I>Microbes</I> include: in-chapter questions that cause students
to pause and think about a concept before proceeding, full color complex processes, and
quizzes at the end of each chapter.
<br clear=left>
