<head>

<title>Interactive Physics II Software</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/physiccv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_physcv.gif"></a>
<BR>
<h2>Interactive Physics II Software</h2>

<h4>Windows Diskettes #34467</h4>
<h4>Macintosh Diskettes #34516</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/physics2.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_phys2.gif"></a>
With <EM>Interactive Physics II</EM>, experiments and demonstrations are as quick and simple as you
want them to be, and as sophisticated as you need them to be.  This simple interface lets
beginners jump right in.  The advanced simulation engine gives you an effective tool for
investigation.  <P>

<EM>Interactive Physics</EM> is an electronic blackboard  where drawings are animated to quickly
simulate realistic motion.  The interface is so easy to use that a beginner can start
immediately by drawing objects, then defining parameters such as mass, friction, gravity, air
resistance, electrostatics and elasticity.  Constraints such as springs, gear,       pulleys, ropes
and motors can be selected to act on the simulation objects according to their designated
parameters.  <P>
<a href="gifs/physics3.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_phys3.gif"></a>
The advanced engine calculates the motion of the system and displays it in smooth animation. 
Meters can be selected to automatically display simulation information in graphical or digital
format as the   simulation runs.  Tabular Data Input lets users run experiments in the lab,
hook the collected data into <EM>Interactive Physics</EM> through standard formats such as Excel, and
simulate the experiment on a computer to compare real results with simulation-     generated
results.<P>
This is physics as it should be.  You're no longer limited by the contents of your equipment
room, or by friction, or by     gravity, or by time, or by      complexity, or by your fixed
frame of reference. <a href="gifs/physics4.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 
src="smgifs/s_phys4.gif"></a> You can perform virtually any experiment, model and problem,
demonstrate any principle, all in clear, smooth,      animated simulations.  With all these
tools at your fingertips, you can demonstrate principles with great clarity, and explore new
questions with unparalleled flexibility.<P>

<EM>Interactive Physics</EM> is powerful and intuitive, offering advanced collision detection and
accuracy checking technology to ensure reliable data.  You can choose from a combination of
accuracy settings to meet the need of simulations performed.  
<br clear=right>
