<h2>BioSource Videodisc</h2>

<h4>Videodisc #22849</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr>Let Wm. C. Brown Publishers bring life sciences into your classroom with this videodisc
showcasing  nearly 10,000 full-color illustrations, photos and    animations.The disc contains
20 minutes of dynamic animated illustrations to help students understand key
physiological concepts of life        science, such as osmosis, actions of the steroid  hormone
on target cells, and the life cycle of HIV.<P>
<i>BioSource Videodisc</i> is logically organized by phyla-logical for your course planning
purposes, and logical for your students as it helps them understand the taxonomy of life
forms.  <P>

It's easy to incorporate visuals from <i>BioSource Videodisc</i> into your presentations.  With
simple-to-use interactive software in both IBM and Macintosh formats, you can efficiently
prepare   lecture notes with barcodes inserted at appropriate points, allowing you to access
directly from your notes whatever videodisc visuals you'd like.<P>

Accompanying the videodisc is a four-volume comprehensive reference manual providing a
sequential listing of all images, their locations on the disc, and barcodes for instant
accessibility.
Common and scientific names are supplied for all images.

