<html>

<head>
<title>Exploring Earth Science</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>

<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br><img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><br>

</center>
<BR>
<a href="gifs/earthcv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_earthcv.gif"></a>

<H2>Exploring Earth Science CD-ROM</H2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #34166</h4>
<h4>(Windows Only)</h4>

<BR clear=left>
<hr>
<a href="gifs/earth1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_earth1.gif"></a><BR>

<I>Exploring Earth Science</I> explores the fascinating story of our planet from its surface
processes to the hidden secrets of the inner earth.  The comprehensive information within
<I>Exploring Earth Science</I>    supports the understanding of physical geography and geology
that includes sections about the Earth's surface, crust, and beneath the surface.<P>

<a href="gifs/earth2.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_earth2.gif"></a>

Students can study and identify rocks within a  question and answer section, which sets the
student on a trail of discovery leading to rock classification.<P>

The Space section provides a complete explanation of the solar system, including full color
photos and informative commentary by Heather Couper, one of the world's leading
astronomers. <P> 

<a href="gifs/earth4.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_earth4.gif"></a>

An interactive star atlas enables the study of the sky with simulated views from anywhere on
earth at any time and into the future.  Star maps showing the constellations are included to
demonstrate how stars change their positions over time.<P>

Satellite information is valuable for teaching many subjects, but is often quite expensive to
acquire.  This program has over 250 indexed satellite images for analysis. <P>

<a href="gifs/earth5.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_earth5.gif"></a>

<I>Exploring Earth Science</I> also provides explanatory sections about satellite technology, and
it's interpretation by earth scientists. <P> 

Students can discover the uses of satellite data in science today, including the interpretation
of weather images through the study of cloud formation.  <P>

<a href="gifs/earth7.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_earth7.gif"></a>

<I>Exploring Earth Science</I> contains over 1,000 text articles, 1,200 color pictures supported by
approximately 30 minutes of audio and 20 minutes of video animation. <P> 

An instructor's guide is also included with this CD-ROM.  It covers, in detail,  how the
CD-ROM may be used in the classroom.<P>

<br clear=right>
<hr>
