<h2>History of American Music CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows or Macintosh CD-ROM #34369</h4>

<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/lit1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_lit1.gif"></a>
<BR>
<EM>American Music</EM> offers a great way to learn more about American history by studying the
music of each era.  This CD enables students to learn more about American music by
studying the history that contributed to its development.  Over 400 complete folk, religious,
and popular compositions are featured, representing over 350 years of history.  

<P>
<a href="gifs/lit4.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_lit4.gif"></a><P>

<B><I>Contents Include:</I></B> <BR>
<ul>
<li><B>Folk Music</B><BR>
(Pioneers, Forty-Niners, Cowboys, Ballads) <BR>

<li><B>African-American</B> <BR>
(Work, Blues, Spirituals, Coal Miners) <BR>

<li><B>Popular Music</B> <BR>
(Ballad, Opera, Bands, Jazz, Country & Western)<BR>

<li><B>Religious Music</B> <BR>
(Psalmody, Gospel, Black Spirituals)<BR>
</ul>
