<a href="gifs/geocv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_geocv.gif"></a>

<h2>Physical Geology CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #24472</h4>
<h4>Macintosh CD-ROM #23726</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/geo3.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_geo3.gif"></a>
<BR>Imagine volcanoes erupting before your students' eyes, or witnessing a formation of a star! 
Now, it is possible with the help of <I>Physical Geology</I>, created by Wm. C. Brown Publishers.
This CD-ROM         contains 21 chapters with material ranging from the motion of plates,
to the growth of crystals from melt, to the weathering and erosion of Earth's surfaces. 
Whether used as a lecture supplement or as a student tutorial, this software's many color
animations help teach some of the most fundamental geological processes and capture the    imagination of today's visually oriented students.  
<a href="gifs/geo5.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_geo5.gif"></a><P>
Students using this software actively participate by answering questions that vary in level of
difficulty, rather than      passively absorbing information.

