<head>

<title>Interactive Plate Tectonics</title>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/techdirect/maps/techdrbr.map"><img border=0 src="/techdirect/gifs/techdrbr.gif" ismap></a><br>
<img src="/techdirect/gifs/mprule.gif"><P>
</center>

<a href="gifs/platecv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_platecv.gif"></a>

<h2>Interactive Plate Tectonics CD-ROM</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #32822</h4>
<h4>Macintosh CD-ROM #32822</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/plate1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_plate1.gif"></a>
<BR>With Wm. C. Brown Publishers' <I>Interactive Plate Tectonics</I> CD-ROM, videos, animations,
photos, maps, audio, and descriptive text lead your students through in-depth case studies
and illustrative tutorials.  This CD focuses on specific geologic characteristics and varying
aspects of the plate tectonics theory.  
<I>Interactive Plate Tectonics</I> also offers maps, outlines, and windows that can be selected to
explore specific geologic characteristics and aspects of plate     tectonics theory using video,
animation, voice-overs, and graphics.  
<a href="gifs/plate4.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_plate4.gif"></a><P>
Graphic case studies of mountain ranges, trenches, sea-floor rifts, faults, and volcanic
activity introduce students to the varying aspects of the plate tectonic       theory.

<br clear=left>
<hr>

