<a href="gifs/bookscv.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_bookscv.gif"></a>
<BR>
<h2>Bookshelf '95</h2>

<h4>Windows CD-ROM #34170</h4>
<h4>Macintosh CD-ROM #34171</h4>
<BR clear=left>
<hr><a href="gifs/books1.gif"><img border=2 align=right hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_books1.gif"></a>
<EM>Bookshelf  '95</EM> redefines reference with lightning-fast searches, easy access to information,
and rich sound, video and animations.  Bookshelf includes the full text of eight best-selling
reference books, including <EM>The American Heritage Dictionary, The Concise Columbia
Encyclopedia, The Original Roget's Thesaurus, The World Almanac and Book of Facts,
1995 Edition, The Columbia Dictionary of Quotations, The People's Chronology, Hammond
Intermediate World Atlas, and  National Five-Digit Zip Code and Post Office Directory</EM>.  
<a href="gifs/books2.gif"><img border=2 align=left hspace=15 vspace=10 src="smgifs/s_books2.gif"></a><P>
<EM>Bookshelf</EM> brings reference to life with video clips, sound, images, and more than 80,000
spoken      pronunciations. Students can copy and paste images, text, or sound into    reports
or classroom     presentations.

<br clear=left>
<hr>

