<title>External Information Resources -- Procurement</title>
<link rev="made" href="mailto:www@itd.nrl.navy.mil">
<h1>External Information Resources -- Procurement</h1>
<h2>GSA</h2>
The General Services Administration's Online Schedule System (OSS)
is a BBS providing information
about some GSA schedules, particularly ADP. Microcomputer-related
schedules are online in their entirety and can be searched; an
especially useful capability lets you list all vendors offering
a particular item, sorted by price, with links to their respective
GSA schedules.
<ul>
<li>
<a href="telnet://oss2.gsa.gov">
access GSA Online Schedule System</a></li>
(type RETURN after you connect)
<li>
<a href="file://localhost/vol/www/filesys/GSA/index.html">
Selected files from Online Schedule System</a>
(local access only)</li>
<li>
Instructions for dialup access are in the
<a href="file://localhost/vol/www/filesys/GSA/OSS_User_Guide">User Guide</a> (local access only).</li>
</ul>
GSA Web servers:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.gsa.gov/">GSA Home Page</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.fss.gsa.gov/">Federal Supply Service</a></li>
</ul>
For general information on OSS and other
topics, you can call the GSA telephone response system at 202-501-1993.
<h2>NASA</h2>
The NASA Scientific and Engineering Workstation Procurement (SEWP)
is a set of giant IDIQ contracts with -- at least in some cases --
very aggressive pricing.  In the past, the Navy has been able to
use this contract up to a yearly allocation, but the limit has usually
been reached very early in the fiscal year.  The online information
may still be useful in other ways, e.g., for comparative pricing.
<ul>
<li>
<a href="http://sewp.nasa.gov/">SEWP HTTP server</a></li>
</ul>
<h2>NRL</h2>
The NRL Library's
<a href="../NRL/online/online-resources.html#INFONT">INFONET</a>
server has some procurement-related
information, e.g., an online copy of Federal Procurement
Regulations.
<hr>
<a href="../"><i>Visit ITD Home Page</i></a>
<p>
Address comments and questions to
<EM><a href="mailto:webmaster@itd.nrl.navy.mil">webmaster@itd.nrl.navy.mil</a></EM>.
<p>
Last updated on 12 March 1996.
