<HEAD>
<Title>THE REALIZATION REPORT: Issue No. 0</Title>
<NEXTID=1>
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1>THE REALIZATION REPORT: 
Issue No. 0</H1>
<hr>
<H3>by
<A HREF = "rosenblum.html">Larry Rosenblum</A>,
<a href="onr.disclaimer.html">ONR FFO European Office</A>
</H3>
<hr><p>
<i>The ONR European Office Computer Science Newsletter that
focuses on
European and Middle Eastern activities in data visualization,
virtual reality, and enabling technologies for these
disciplines.
</i>
<hr><p>

<PRE>
                         28 October 1992
</PRE>

Hello from London!
<P>

I'm Larry Rosenblum and I've accepted a 19 month assignment as
Liaison Scientist (Computer Science) at the Office of Naval
Research European Office.  I'm on leave from the Naval Research
Laboratory in Washington DC.  My focus is data visualization,
virtual reality, and their enabling technologies.
<P>

As part of my responsibilities, I will be issuing e-mail reports on
European research in these focal areas.  These reports will
frequently be trip reports of visits to institutions in Europe,
describing the research seen.  Less often, they will be
conference/workshop reports, or reports on computer science topics
of interest obtained from other sources.  The reports are intended
to assist both computer science researchers and managers.  Please
note that while every effort is made to be accurate, emphasis will
be placed rapidly disseminating information.
<P>

My goal is to help the U.S. research community maintain a current
awareness of European activities and to encourage liaison and
discussion between research groups across the Atlantic.  I welcome
your feedback on a variety of topics:  Do you know someone in
Europe doing leading, original research who should be visited for
a report?  Do you have any other comments or recommendations?  My
time here is limited, so I might not be able to respond to every
recommendation or inquiry -- but I'll do my best and your input is
valued!
<P>

Do you know others who might like to be added to the distribution
list?  If so, let me know.  If the reports are not of interest and
you would like you your name removed (you might have a better idea
after a few reports!) let me know that also.
<P>

I will appreciate (I hope!) any feedback that you take the time to
give me, and I look forward to providing you with useful
information on important happenings in Europe.
<P>

Regards to all,
<P>

Larry
<P>

<hr>
<hr>
<p>
<p>

<b>Standard Report Navigation</b><P>

<UL>
  <LI><a href="rosenblum.001.html">To Next Report</a>
  <LI><a href="rosenblum.toc.html">To Rosenblum Index</a>
</UL>
<p>

<b>Related Realization Reports</b><P>

</DOC>
<DOC>
