<PRE>
</PRE>

Abstract:  This report lists some upcoming European workshops and
conferences covering computer graphics, virtual reality,
multimedia, and related topics.
<P>

<PRE>
               _________________________________
</PRE>

Graphics and Visualization Techniques and Tools
(UK Advisory Group on Computer Graphics)
<P>

A one week residential course designed to give students an
appreciation of effective ways of visually displaying data, to
introduce some basics of 3D modelling and rendering, and to provide
practical experience.  <a href="rosenblum.003.html">REALIZATION REPORT #3</a> discussed activities
at the Univ. of Leeds.
<P>

<PRE>
	10-14 January 1994
</PRE>
	Univ. of Leeds, Leeds, UK
	Contact:  Ken Brodlie, kwb@scs.leeds.ac.uk
<P>

IEE Colloquium on Human Factors in the Application of Graphical
User Interfaces.  "What are GUI's Good For?"
<P>

<PRE>
	27 January 1994
</PRE>
	London, UK
	Contact Simon Hakiel, hakiel@winvmd.vnet.ibm.com
