	Bari, Italy
	Contact: T. Catarci, catarci@infokit.ing.uniromal.it
<P>

6th ERCIM Workshop
<P>

ERCIM is the European Consortium on Informatics and Mathematics, an
association of European research laboratories promoting cooperative
research on key issues in information technology.  Members are
AEDIMA (Spain), CRN (Italy), CWI(Netherlands), FORTH (Greece), GMD
(Germany), INESC (Portugal), INRIA (France), RAL (UK), SICS
(Sweden), SINTEF (Norway), and VTT (Finland).  Work from CWI,
INRIA, and GMD have been reported on in earlier Realization
Reports.
<P>

The Workshop objective is to bring together researchers and
industrial practitioners to identify and discuss key technology
issues in selected areas.  The 6th set of ERCIM Workshop are:
<P>

<PRE>
    Distributed Virtual Environments Workshop
    Personnel Computing and Communications Environments Workshop
    High-Performance Communications Workshop
</PRE>

Audio and video will be broadcast over the Internet Mbone
worldwide.  These sessions will be announced via 'sd' over Mbone.
Information on how to prepare for this can be obtained by picking
up the file isi.edu:pub/mbone/faq.txt
<P>

<PRE>
	1-3 June 1994
</PRE>
	Stockholm-Kista, Electrum, Sweden
	Contact: Bjorn Pehrson, bjorn@it.kth.se
<P>

Applications of Virtual Reality (British Computer Society Displays
Group)
<P>

A continuation to the June 1992 meeting which formed the basis for
the 1993 book "Virtual Reality Systems" (Academic Press) edited by
Rae Earnshaw, Mike Gigante, and Huw Jones.  This meeting will focus
on applications.
<P>

<PRE>
	7-9 June 1994
</PRE>
	London, UK
	Contact:  Huw Jones, huw1@cluster.mdx.ac.uk
