<head>
<TITLE>High Assurance Workshop Reports</Title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#0000FF" vlink="#871F78" alink="#FF0000">

<img src="../gifs/colorline.gif">
<p>

<h1>High Assurance Workshop Reports</h1>

<p>
<img src="../gifs/colorline.gif">
<p>
<a href="../publications/HighAssurWkshpRepts/summary-report.ps"><font size=4>Summary Report</a> <font size=2>[PostScript]
<p>
<font size=3>
McLean, J and Heitmeyer, C. "High Assurance Computer Systems: A Research Agenda," America in the Age of Information, National Science and Technology Council Committee on Information and Communications Forum, Bethesda, 1995.
<blockquote>
       Many scientific approaches for specifying, constructing, and certifying high assurance systems have been developed, including formal verification and validation techniques. Much still needs to be done with respect to individual critical properties (e.g., safety, security, and timeliness). Even more needs to be done with respect to (1) the lack of technology support for applying these techniques to practical, real-word systems, and (2) the lack of a unified framework for building systems that satisfy several critical properties. These problems are of such a difficult nature that they will not be solved by industry or academia without the support of both government funding agencies and government research laboratories. This paper summarizes the results of a workshop in which a group of 50 experts from academia, government, and industry participated to address these challenges. 
</blockquote>
<p>
<a href="../publications/HighAssurWkshpRepts/dependability-report.ps"><font size=4>Dependability Track Report</a> <font size=2>[PostScript]
<p>
<a href="../publications/HighAssurWkshpRepts/security-report.ps"><font size=4>Security Track Report</a> <font size=2>[PostScript]
<p>
<a href="../publications/HighAssurWkshpRepts/safety-report.ps"><font size=4>Safety Track Report</a> <font size=2>[PostScript]
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<font size=3>
<a href="../main.html"><img align=center src="../gifs/branch-icon.GIF"> Home Page</a>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<ADDRESS>Mark McBride / mcbride@itd.nrl.navy.mil/ Last Modified: 30 May 1996
</ADDRESS>
<p>
