<html>
<head>
<Title>Computer Security Section (Code 5542)</Title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#0000FF" vlink="#871F78" alink="#FF0000">

<img src="../gifs/colorline.gif">
<p>
<font color="#8C1717"><H1>Computer Security Section (Code 5542)</H1>
<p>
<img src="../gifs/colorline.gif">
<p>
<font color="#000000">
This page is part of the web for the
<a href="../index.html">
 Center for High Assurance Computer Systems</a>.
<p>
<HR>
<p>
The Computer Security Section conducts research leading to improved 
methods for specifying, designing, implementing, verifying, and
certifying computer systems that must enforce security requirements. 
A fundamental question that motivates many of our projects is, "How can 
we write computer programs or build computer systems and know what they do?"
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<font color="#42426F"><H1>Personnel</H1>
<p>
<ul>
<font color="#000000">
  <li> <a href="../personnel/landwehr.html">
        Carl E. Landwehr</a>, <font color="#CD7F32"><b>Section Head</b>
  <li> <font color="#000000">Judith N. Froscher
  <li> Myong Kang
  <li> John P. McDermott
  <li> <a href="../personnel/moore.html">
        Andrew P. Moore</a>
  <li> <a href="../personnel/reed/">Michael G. Reed</a>
</ul>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<font color="#42426F">
<H1>Projects</H1>
<p>
<DL>
<font color="#000000">
<DT><a href="../projects/dhabb.html">
<ul>
<li><b>Developing High Assurance Building Blocks (DHABB)</b></a>
<DD> Applying formal methods, including formal specifications and
automated reasoning tools, to the problem of developing hardware/software 
building blocks that can be certified to enforce specified
critical properties with a high degree of assurance.
<p>
<li><DT><a href="../projects/haset.html">
     <b>High Assurance System Engineering Techniques (HASET)</b></a>
<DD> Developing new methods for identifying, recording, and reasoning 
about security engineering tradeoffs at the system level.
<p>
<li><DT><a href="../projects/sintra.html">
     <b>Secure Information Through Replicated Architecture (SINTRA)</b></a>
<DD> Exploring hardware replication as a practical approach to multilevel
secure database systems and information systems generally.
</ul>
</DL>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<font color="#42426F"><H1>Publications</H1>
<p>
<font color="#000000">
Our publications are included in the 
<a href="../publications/index.html">
 overall list</a> for the 
<a href="../index.html">
 Center for High Assurance Computer Systems</a>.  If you know the project
responsible for the publication, follow the appropriate project link above
for a list of publications by project.
<p>
<img src="../gifs/colorline.gif">
<p>
<a href="../organization.html"><img align=center src="../gifs/back.gif"></a> Return to the Organization Page.
</body>
</html>
