<html>
<head>
<Title>Formal Methods Section (Code 5543)</Title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#0000FF" vlink="#871F78" alink="#FF0000">

<p>
<img src="../gifs/colorline.gif">
<p>
<font color="#8C1717"><H1>Formal Methods Section (Code 5543)</H1>
<p>
<img src="../gifs/colorline.gif">
<p>
<font color="#000000">
This page is part of the web for the
<a href="../index.html">
 Center for High Assurance Computer Systems</a>.
<p>
<HR>
<p>
The Formal Methods Section is responsible for research and consultation  
in formal methods for high assurance systems, including computer
security model development and analysis, software specification and
verification, covert channel analysis, cryptographic protocol analysis,
and information theory.
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<font color="#42426F"><H1>Personnel</H1>
<p>
<ul>
<font color="#000000">
  <li> Catherine Meadows, <font color="#CD7F32"><b>Section Head</b>
  <li> <font color="#000000">David Goldschlag
  <li> Steven Greenwald
  <li> Ira Moskowitz
  <li> Paul Syverson
</ul>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<font color="#42426F"><H1>Research Areas</H1>
<p>
<font color="#000000">
Current research areas include:
<ul> 
  <li> Formal Models of Computer Security (POC John McLean)
  <li> Software Tools for Analyzing Cryptographic Protocols 
       (POC Catherine Meadows)
  <li> Logics for Analyzing Cryptographic Protocols (POC Paul Syverson)
  <li> Covert Channel Analysis  (POC Ira Moskowitz) 
  <li> Formal Verification (POC David Goldschlag) 
</ul>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<font color="#42426F"><H1>Publications</H1>
<p>
<font color="#000000">
A list of our publications will be provided soon.
<p>
<img src="../gifs/colorline.gif">
<p>
<a href="../organization.html"><img align=center src="../gifs/back.gif"></a> Return to the Organization Page.
<p>
</body>
