<H1>Navy Handbook for the Computer Security Certification of Trusted 
Systems</H1>

<p> 

This page is part of the web for the 
<a href="http://www.itd.nrl.navy.mil/ITD/5540/">
 Center for High Assurance Computing Systems</a>.

<p>

<hr>

<p>

The chapters listed below are provided in two portable formats: Adobe
PostScript and Adobe PDF (Portable Document Format).  The PDF files
can be viewed on any Mac, Windows or Sun machine using <a
href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/readstep.html">freely available reader
software</a> from Adobe.  

<P> 

In general, a PDF file is smaller and, with the reader, easier to
peruse online than the corresponding PostScript file.  You may also
print from the PDF viewer.  Some PostScript viewers (e.g., Pageview)
on the other hand, may not display some of the PostScript files properly,
although all files should print fine.  Both formats are type ASCII.

