Benzel, T. C. Vickers (Trusted Information Systems, Inc.). Developing 
Trusted Systems Using DOD-STD-2167A. in: 5th Annual Computer 
Security Applications Conference; 1989 Dec; Tucson, Arizona. USA: IEEE 
Computer Society Press; 1989: pp.166-176. ISBN: 0-8186-2006-4.
This paper describes a software development process for developing 
trusted systems under DOD_STD_2167A. The process is based on an 
approach which integrates Trusted Computer System Evaluation 
Criteria requirements into the software development process required 
by DOD-STD-2167A. The process described in this paper focuses on 
development of DOD-STD-2167A Data Item Deliverables which have 
been tailored to include TCSEC deliverables. The paper describes how 
these items can be produced in a manner which minimizes the impact 
on cost and budget, while increasing assurance in the product's 
trustworthiness.
/Software Development/Trusted Systems/TCSEC.

