Bodeau, Deborah J.; Brusil, Nancy R.; Chang, Irene N.; Reece, Mary Jo (The 
MITRE Corporation). Security Test and Evaluation for Multilevel-Mode 
Accredition : Lessons Learned. 8th Annual Computer Security 
Applications Conference; 1930 Nov 4; San Antonio, Texas. USA: IEEE 
Computer Society Press; 1992: pp. 37-45. ISBN: 0-8186-3115-5.
In this paper, we describe MITRE's experience and lessons learned in 
performing Security Test and Evaluation (ST&E) for SPADOC 4B. ST&E 
drew on contractual testing but involved extensive government testing 
of the system. ST&E included testing in a representative stressed 
environment and in failure situations. ST&E also involved verification 
of safeguards from security disciplines other than COMPUSEC, including 
procedural and physical security. SPADOC 4B has been accredited to 
operate in multilevel mode.
