Bowen, Jonathan; Gimson, Roger; Topp-Jorgensen, Stig. The 
Specification of Network Services. 1987. 
Oxford University Computing Laboratory, Programming Research Group 
PRG-61
The specification language Z has been applied by the Distributed 
Computing Software Project to the formal specification of network 
resource managers or 'services'. The use of a formal language gives a 
more precise understanding of the behaviour of a service and is a 
prerequisite for verification of programs which use or implement the 
service. Additionally, the use of Z combined with informal text is 
sufficiently readable for the specification to be used for 
documentation purposes.
An introduction is provided to the style of specification devised for the 
project. A framework for the specification of a variety of network 
services has been developed. The framework is presented, and then 
incorporated into an example illustrating the specification of both the 
user's view and the implementor's view of a simple service. A 
discussion of the experience gained from the specification and use of 
example service is also included.
T629,T789. 
formal specification/networks/protocols/Z. 

