Boyer, Robert S.; Moore, J. S. A Computational Logic. 1977. 
Academic Press
0-12-122950-5
This book presents the logic system that underlies the SRI Boyer-Moore 
mechanical theorem prover. It attempts to show how the logic can be 
used to prove theorems rather than presenting the proofs of specific 
results. It illustrates a number of proof techniques, including 
simplification, generalisation and the use of induction. It is claimed 
that the illustrative proofs in the book were all produced using the 
Boyer-Moore theorem prover.
/mathematics/theorem proving/Boyer-Moore. 

