Denning, Dorothy E.; Akl, Selim G.; Morgenstern, M.; Neumann, Peter G.; 
Schell, Roger R.; Heckman, Mark. Views for Multilevel Database 
Security. 1986 Apr. 
IEEE Comp. Soc. Proc. 1986 Symp. Security and Privacy pp.156-172
The aim of the work underlying the paper is to design a MLS/DBMS 
based on protected views using relational model. The paper describes 
views and summarises the motivation for using them. Classification 
can be attached to views and then these act as rules for adding 
classification information when updating the database. There is a 
significant problem in ensuring this labelling technique is complete and 
consistent. The paper also discusses how views can be used to control 
aggregation, and ends with a sketch of a tentative design for a system 
that is hoped to be A1 secure.
/security/multilevel security/databases/relational 
databases/multilevel databases/views. 

