Goldberg, J. SIFT: a provable fault-tolerant computer for aircraft flight 
control. 1980. 
in: Information Processing 80, S H Lavington (ed) North-Holland 
Publishing Company IFIP
SIFT (Software Implemented Fault Tolerance) is an experimental fault-
tolerant computer system for flight control of advanced aircraft 
including those that are inherently unstable. Such a computer must be 
extremely reliable.
Life-testing and exhaustive testing of such a computer are both 
impossible. To justify their claims of high reliability the designers of 
SIFT have had to verify that the design is consistent with the required 
fault-tolerant behaviour.
This paper first outlines the basic fault-tolerance approach, the design 
philosophy, the hardware and software structures used. It then 
describes the way in which the design was verified
/formal specification/Verification/SIFT/Fault 
Tolerance/architectures/reliability. 

