Gosselin, Michelle J. (The MITRE Corporation). The Development of a 
Low-to-High Guard. in: 14th National Computer Security Conference; 
1991 Oct; Washington. USA: NIST/NCSC; 1991; 1: pp.157-166. 
This report details the development of a guard to monitor electronic 
traffic between two computer systems. The guard is intended to 
operate between two computer systems that are accredited to operate 
at different security levels. One system (the high system) must be 
accredited to process all information on the other system (the low 
system). The purpose of the guard is to automate the delivery of 
information from the low system to the high system while preventing 
any flow of information from the high system to the low system.
/Guards/Accreditation.

