Harrison, Linda J. (Unisys Corporation). Security Issues and Ada 
Runtime Support. in: 5th Annual Computer Security Applications 
Conference; 1989 Dec; Tucson, Arizona. USA: IEEE Computer Society 
Press; 1989: pp.177-183. ISBN: 0-8186-2006-4.
This paper reports on an investigation of the security issues related to 
Ada runtime support. First, the need to use Ada features requiring 
runtime support is motivated. The paper then describes how the Ada 
Runtime Library in the development environment is transformed to 
become the Ada Runtime System in the operational environment. Key 
security requirements, such as protection of the runtime library in the 
development environment, and design of a security architecture in the 
operational environment are examined. The paper concludes that further 
research is required along with the actual development of trusted Ada 
Runtime Systems.
/Software Development/Ada/Trusted Systems.

