Herzberg, A.; Pinter, S. S. Public Protection of Software. 1987 Nov. 
ACM Transactions on Computer Systems
One of the overwhelming problems that software producers must 
contend with is the unauthorized use and distribution of their products. 
Copyright laws concerning software are rarely enforced, thereby 
causing major losses to the software companies. Technical means of 
protecting software from illegal duplication are required, but the 
available means are imperfect. We present protocols that enable 
software protection, without causing substantial overhead in 
distribution and maintenance. The protocols may be implemented by a 
conventional cryptosystem, such as the DES, or by a public key 
cryptosystem, such as the RSA. Both implementations ar proved to 
satisfy required security criteria.
/Crypto/Software Protection. 

