Without going into detail, the paper describes the various steps in the 
design and verification of a 32-bit microprocessor chip. While not 
using the latest tools - the work reported was completed in 1983 - it 
is an interesting description of a real-life large-scale verification 
project, illustrating what is feasible in hardware verification.
