Lam, Simon S.; Shankar, A. Udaya; Woo, Thomas Y. C. (University of 
Texas & University of Maryland). Applying a Theory of Modules and 
Interfaces to Security Verification. in: 1991 IEEE Computer Society 
Symposium on Research in Security and Privacy; 1991 May; Oakland, 
California. USA: IEEE Computer Society Press; 1991: pp.136-154. ISBN: 
0-8186-2168-0.
We present an overview of a theory of modules and interfaces 
applicable to the specification and verification of systems with a 
layered architecture. At the heart of this theory is a module 
composition theorem. The theory is applied to the specification of a 
distributed system consisting of subjects and objects in different 
hosts (computers). Formal specifications of a user interface and a 
network interface are given. Access to objects, both local and remote, 
offered by the distributed system is proved to be multilevel secure.
/Distributed 
Systems/Modules/Interfaces/Specification/Verification/Layered 
Architecture.

