This collection of lectures deals with a number of important topics in 
distributed computing, each being presented by a single author. The 
lectures are independent of each other, which results in a certain 
amount of duplication, but do cover a great deal of ground. An extensive 
bibliography is included.
Amongst the topics included are a number touching on aspects of 
reliable and secure systems such as naming, protection (which deals 
primarily with encryption but includes consideration of access control 
methods such as capabilities), atomic transactions and 
synchronization.
