Landwehr, Carl E. What security levels are for and why integrity levels 
are unnecessary. 1982 Feb. 
NRL-7590-308:CL:uni, Naval Research Lab, Washington DC
This two-page memo is by the person who was responsible for drawing 
up a security model for the military message experiment. In it he 
argues that the need to handle security levels is the direct result of 
policies mandated by government directive, whereas there is no such 
mandatory need for integrity levels. For this reason, and because he 
believes that integrity levels are not the right approach, he proposed to 
omit them from the model; the requirements for integrity would be 
covered by specific assertions as needed.
/security/integrity/security levels/integrity levels/security models. 

