Lewis, Sharon R.; Wiseman, Simon R.; Poulter, Neil D. (Defense Research 
Agency,Malvern, UK). Providing Security in a Phone Book Database Using 
Triggers. 8th Annual Computer Security Applications Conference; 1930 
Nov 4; San Antonio, Texas. USA: IEEE Computer Society Press; 1992: pp. 
85-96. ISBN: 0-8186-3115-5.
It is proposed that all database security controls, except those which 
provide information flow security, can be built using a suitable trigger 
mechanism. The implementation of an example application, which has a 
variety of requirements for confidentiality, integrity and 
accountability, is shown to illustrate the technique. The trigger 
mechanism is to be implemented using query modification as part of 
the SWORD secure DBMS project.
