Liu, M. T.; Reames, C. C. Message Communication Protocol and Operating 
System Design for the Distributed Loop Computer Network (DLCN). 1977 
Mar. 
ACM SIGARCH 5(7) Proc. 4th Symp. Computer Architecture
The DLCN is envisaged as a powerful, unified distributed computing 
system which interconnects heterogeneous midi/mini/micro-
computers etc. This paper gives an overview of the design requirements 
and implementation techniques for DLCNs, message protocol and 
network operating system.
It is a hypothetical system to be used to investigate fundamental 
questions of distributed computing. Its description varies between very 
detailed (the message protocol) to completely general. Probably 
reflecting the achievements current at the time of reporting.
This paper is an interesting example of the design of a distributed 
system, but has no specific computer security implications.
