Lunt, Teresa F.; Tamaru, Ann; Gilham, Fred; Jagannathan; Neumann, Peter 
G.; Jalali, Caveh (SRI International). IDES: A Progress Report. in: 6th 
Annual Computer Security Applications Conference; 1990 Dec; Tucson, 
Arizona. USA: IEEE Computer Society Press; 1990: pp.273-285. ISBN: 0-
8186-2105-2.
This paper describes a real-time Intrusion Detection Expert System 
(IDES) that observes user behavior on a monitored computer system and 
adaptively learns what is normal for individual users, groups, remote 
hosts, and the overall system behavior. Observed behavior is flagged as 
a potential intrusion if it deviates significantly from the expected 
behavior or if it triggers a rule in the expert system rule base.
/Intrusion Detection/IDES.

Lunt, Theresa (SRI). Issues of Concurrency Control and Labeling in 
Multilevel Database Systems. in: 13th National Computer Security 
Conference; 1990 Oct 1; Washington. USA: NIST; 1990; 2: 581-584. 

Lunt, Theresa (SRI). Object-Oriented System Security. in: 13th National 
