Lunt, Theresa F.; Denning, D. E.; Schell, R. R.; Heckman, M.; Shockley, W. R. 
The Sea View Security Model. IEEE Trans. on Software Engineering. 1990 
Jun; 16(6): 593-607.
Note: Revised version of IEEE Symposium paper.
A multilevel database is intended to provide the security needed for 
database systems that contain data at a variety of classifications and 
serve a set of users having different clearances.  This paper describes 
a formal security model for such a system.  The model is formulated in 
two layers, one corresponding to a reference monitor that enforces 
mandatory security, and the second an extension of the standard 
relational model, defining multilevel relations and formalising policies 
for labeling new and derived data, data consistency and discretionary 
security.  The model also defines application-independent properties 
for entity integrity, referential integrity and polyinstantiation 
integrity.
/Classification/database security/multilevel 
security/protection/relational databases/security/security model.

