Millen, Jonathan K.; Lunt, Teresa F. (MITRE Corporation & SRI 
International). Security for Object-Oriented Database Systems. in: 1992 
IEEE Symposium on Research in Security and Privacy; 1992 May 4; 
Oakland, California. USA: IEEE Computer Society Press; 1992: pp. 260. 
A multilevel object-oriented system can be implemented on a 
conventional mandatory security kernel. Each object is assigned a 
single security level that applies to all its contents (variables and 
methods). The informal security policy model includes properties such 
