Nestor, John P. (University of Toronto). Security Modelling Using 
Hierarchical State Machines. in: 7th Annual Computer Security 
Applications Conference; 1991 Dec; San Antonio, Texas. USA: IEEE 
Computer Society Press; 1991: pp.110-119. ISBN: 0-8186-2280-6.
This paper defines a modelling scheme that allows for abstraction to 
simplify security analysis, while at the same time permitting a full 
description of detailed system behaviour. The basis for the model is a 
hierarchy of state machines. The security equivalence of the varying 
levels of abstraction is proven, thereby demonstrating the validity of 
the model. Also, practical considerations regarding the application of 
the model to real systems are presented.
/security models/Hierarchical State Machines/Formal Methods.

