This book presents a classification of threats in computer systems and 
a brief analysis of the sorts of problems in each area. This is then 
backed up with a very comprehensive survey of known cases of 
computer failures of all sorts, and a review picking out interesting and 
significant cases. It concludes with an analysis and guidelines for 
system design. Very well worth reading.
