Ody, Nicholas J. Hardware, Software and 'Trust'. 1987. 
Terms such as 'multi-class trusted hardware' are used in different 
ways in different contexts. The distinctions between hardware, 
software and the data they handle, and the degree of trust placed in 
each, are not always carefully observed.
This document puts forward meanings for 'trust', and identifies some 
commonly used categories of trusted hardware and software. Examples 
are given in the context of processing classified data, but some of the 
concepts should be more generally applicable.
