Okamoto, T.; Shiraishi, A. A Fast Signature Scheme Based on Quadratic 
Inequalities. 1985. 
Yokosuka ECL, NTT
IEEE Comp. Soc. Proc. 1985 Symp. Security and Privacy pp.123-133
A signature scheme is expected to guard against two risks: C pretends 
to be A, sending message to B; and, B forges signature, claims 
messages came from A. Schemes using RSA encryption algorithm have 
been designed, but the algorithm is slow. Other proposed schemes are 
either suspected of being unsafe (viz Shamir's based on trapdoor 
knapsacks) or about as slow as the RSA-based scheme. The scheme 
proposed in this paper is approximately 100 times faster than the RSA 
scheme, and is intended to have comparable key/signature lengths and 
security.
The scheme is based on quadratic inequalities, and appears to have 
potential. It has yet to be implemented, and would require independent 
mathematical analysis before any reliance is placed on its security.
/digital signatures. 

