Otwell, Ken; Aldridge, Bruce (Martin Marietta Laboratories and 
Information & Communications Systems). The Role of Vulnerability in 
Risk Management. in: 5th Annual Computer Security Applications 
Conference; 1989 Dec; Tucson, Arizona. USA: IEEE Computer Society 
Press; 1989: pp.32-38. ISBN: 0-8186-2006-4.
Developing a formal definition of vulnerability to provide a basis for 
information system risk management has proven to be a complex 
process. In this paper, we examine the treatment of vulnerability at the 
1988 Risk Model Builders' Workshop and develop a definition that is 
intuitively satisfying and provides a foundation upon which 
mathematical models can be built. We present two such vulnerability 
models that together appear to capture the general conceptualizations 
of vulnerability espoused by other authors.
