Parks, J. R. Biometrics: The People Sensors. Sensor Review. 1989 Apr; 
9(2): 79.
Note: Abstract in TechGnosis, June 1989 (PO689-58).
Biometrics, the statistical or quantitative study of behavioural and 
physical characteristics is being used increasingly to discriminate 
between individuals and can be used as a supplement to a PIN or a 
smart card.  The term now used to describe such methods of 
verification is Positive Biometrics Identification 
(PBI).  This paper examines PBI applications, namely voice, 
fingerprinting, vein patterns (on the wrist/hand or the retina), 
keyboard rhythm, hand geometry, and signatures.  An appendix lists 
commercially available biometric devices and their vendors (eg IBM, 
TITN, Confirma, ECCO, Esselte, Palmguard, Quest, Voxtron Systems, 
Fingermatrix, Eye D, British Technology Group and PIDEAC).
/security/authentication/identification/biometric identification.

