Note: This paper discusses a number of recommendations for increasing 
the general level of security awareness of the workforce at a sensitive 
site. These include memorable advertising to staff of security 
procedures; the most memorable advertising posters are the best and 
the worst. There are also recommendations about the form and content 
of security briefings to new and existing staff, again with the accent 
on memorability.
	Management awareness of security issues is of course an 
important part of the security officer's brief: there are three aspects 
to the security officer's job in dealing with management: make 
management aware of its responsibilities; advise on the realistic 
consequences of not meeting those responsibilities; and, take good 
notes.
	The security officer is advised to make himself visible to the 
employees at their various workplaces, to be available to answer 
questions, and to look out for: the more than usually cooperative ('thank 
you') and the more than usually uncooperative ('make them an offer they 
can't refuse').

