/data protection. 

Rivest, R. L.; Shamir, A.; Adleman, Len M. A method for obtaining digital 
signatures and public key cryptosystems. 1978 Feb. 
CACM 21(2) pp.120-126 CACM 26(1) Anniversary issue pp.96-99
Also MIT/LCS/TM 82, Technical memo, MIT
This paper describes the first - and so far (1985), the safest - 
algorithm for public-key encryption; it is based on the use of 
exponentiation in modular arithmetic. It contains a detailed analysis of 
the security of the algorithm, showing that cryptanalysis is equivalent 
in difficulty to factorising large numbers. The paper also describes the 
theory of public-key encryption, and how it can be used for privacy and 
signatures; this is based on the paper by Diffie and Hellman.
2T65. 
crypto/RSA/public key/key paper/modular arithmetic/digital 
signatures. 

