Rochlis, Jon A.; Eichin, Mark W. With Microscope and Tweezers: The 
Worm fro MIT's Perspective. CACM. 1989 Jun; 32(6): 689-699.

Roe, Michael; Casey, Tom (University of Cambridge & University College 
London). Integrating Cryptography in the Trusted Computing Base. in: 
6th Annual Computer Security Applications Conference; 1990 Dec; 
Tucson, Arizona. USA: IEEE Computer Society Press; 1990: pp.50-56. 
ISBN: 0-8186-2105-2.
Secure distributed systems are not easily constructed, as they combine 
mechanisms based on very different theories of security (encryption 
and reference monitors). We show how these mechanisms may be 
integrated via the Unix STREAMS mechanism. Examples are given of how 
this architecture can support existing security protocols, and it is 
shown why it is consistent with the Bell-LaPadula and Biba 
information-flow models.
/crypto/TCB/distributed systems/UNIX STREAMS.

Rogers, H. L. (National Security Agency). An Overview of the Caneware 
Program. 10th National Computer Security Conference: Computer 
