Rudell, M. E. Labelling Screen Output. 1985. 
MITRE Corp Bedford MA
IEEE Comp. Soc. Proc. 1985 Symp. Security and Privacy pp.237-240
When displaying results from queries to a (relational) database 
containing multilevel data in a tabular manner, there is sometimes a 
need to display the security labels applicable to the various fields. This 
labelling has to be done in a way that is both unobtrusive and clear, so 
that the user's view of the data and of important labels is not obsured. 
This paper describes one way this can be done using exception marking, 
with letters for sensitivity levels and numbered footnotes for 
category/caveat information.
/Security Labels/Security/Multilevel 
Security/Marking/Databases/Database Output. 

