Sandhu, R.; Share, M. E. Some Owner Based Schemes with Dynamic 
Groups in the Schematic Protection Model. 1986 Apr. 
IEEE Comp. Soc. Proc. 1986 Symp. Security and Privacy pp.61-70
The Schematic Protection Model (SPM) regards a system as a set of 
subjects and objects, with operations on objects authorised by 
possession of tickets (address/rights combinations). A scheme is a 
static set of rules for aquiring tickets.
The paper claims that groups are a good way of specifying requisite 
file protection, provided the grouping is readily specifiable and 
alterable by normal users; it then uses SPM to specify a number of 
different policies, differing mainly in the dynamics of group 
membership.
