Schaefer, Lorrayne J. (The MITRE Corporation). Employee Privacy and 
Intrusion Detection Systems: Monitoring on the Job. in: 14th National 
Computer Security Conference; 1991 Oct; Washington. USA: NIST/NCSC; 
1991; 1: pp.188-194. 
The area of intrusion detection systems and privacy has always had a 
conflict of interest. Intrusion detection systems are designed to help 
the System Security Officer detect malicious or unauthorised use of a 
computer system by both unauthorised and authorised users. These 
systems protect our computer systems from abuse, yet in doing so, it 
violates our privacy. This paper discusses the legal and ethical issues 
involved in using an intrusion detection system to monitor the 
computer system.
/Intrusion Detection/Law/Ethics/Privacy.

