A good paper that lives up to its title. The areas covered are: a review 
of the problem; security requirements; security models; external 
protection mechanisms (administrative controls and physical security); 
internal protection mechanisms (authentication, access control, 
surveillance and communications security); reliability; internal 
protection mechanism requirements (completeness, tamperproofness 
and verification); and, finally, integrity
