Smith, Gary W. (George Mason University). Multilevel Secure Database 
Design: A Practical Application. in: 5th Annual Computer Security 
Applications Conference; 1989 Dec; Tucson, Arizona. USA: IEEE 
Computer Society Press; 1989: pp.314-321. ISBN: 0-8186-2006-4.
The second Rome Air Development Center (RADC) Database Security 
Workshop, held in May 1989, featured a "Homework Problem". The 
Homework Problem was a 22 page specification for a multilevel secure 
(MLS) database. Solutions to the Homework Problem were provided by 
many of the major research and development efforts in MLS database 
systems. This paper describes the requirements of the Homework 
Problem and summarizes the database design approaches taken to meet 
those requirements.
/databases/multilevel security.

