Stubblebine, Staurt G.; Gligor, Virgil D. (University of Maryland). On 
Message Integrity in Cryptographic Protocols. in: 1992 IEEE Computer 
Society Symposium on Research into Security and Privacy; 1992 May 4; 
Oakland, California. USA: IEEE Computer Society Press; 1992: pp. 85. 
We present an operational model for message integrity in cryptographic 
protocols, discuss message integrity requirements, and suggest 
message structures that satisfy those requirements. We derive a 
message splicing/decomposition invariant of the Cipher Block Chaining 
(CBC) mode of encryption, and use it to identify heretofore unknown 
vulnerabilities of well known protocols. The suggested message 
structures remove these vulnerabilities.
8699/T1304.

Stubblebine, Stuart G.; Gligor, Virgil D. (USC Information Sciences 
Institute, CA//
Electrical Engineering Dept., University of Maryland). Protocal Design 
for Integrity Protection. 1993 IEEE Computer Society Symposium on
Research on Security and Privacy; 1993 May 24; Oakland, California. 
USA: IEEE Computer Society; 1993: pp. 41-53. ISBN: 0-8186-3370-0.
We present a design method for message integrity protection.
We illustrate the use of the method by designing large classes of 
message types whose integrity is provably preserved and by applying 
the method to the symmetric key option of the Privacy-enhanced 
Electronic Mail protocol to help discover and eliminate an integrity 
vulnerability.
/Integrity protection.

