Thompson, K. Reflections on trusting trust. 1984 Aug. 
CACM 27(8) pp.761-763
This amusing little paper by one of the originators of UNIX describes 
how to insert trapdoors and trojan horses in programs with very little 
chance of detection. You modify the compiler so that it recognises when 
it is compiling itself, and inserts code that will do this and will also 
recognise and modify another program (such as the logon control 
software).
