Topexpress. The External Architecture of the CMSB: a Z Specification. 
1987. 
TXSG-87-16, Topexpress Ltd
In the entity layer all information flow to and from the entities takes 
place through the CMSB; such information flows are concerned with the 
management of sessions, and communication between sessions. It is 
the purpose of the CMSB to ensure that these information flows accord 
with the security policy. This document specifies in Z notation the 
functionality of the CMSB as perceived by a connected entity. The CMSB 
is modelled as a state machine whose states are altered by operators, 
which are invoked by the entities, in conjunction with packets of 
information, called primitives, that pass between the CMSB and the 
entities concerned.
/security/multilevel security/networks/distributed systems/formal 
specification/Z. 

