Vetter, Linda; Smith, Gordon; Lunt, Teresa F. (Oracle Corporation & SRI 
International). TCB Subsets: The Next Step. in: 5th Annual Computer 
Security Applications Conference; 1989 Dec; Tucson, Arizona. USA: IEEE 
Computer Society Press; 1989: pp.216-221. ISBN: 0-8186-2006-4.
In a TCB subsetting approach, no part of the database system itself is 
involved in enforcing mandatory security. Instead, a previously verified 
mandatory security kernel is used. This approach places severe 
constraints on the architecture of the database system. Particular 
areas of difficulty are concurrency controls, recovery management, and 
buffer management. This paper discusses these issues.
/databases/TCB.

Vick, Ricki Andrew (HFS Inc.). An Overview of the AMC WWMCCS CAT 
Guard. 8th Annual Computer Security Applications Conference; 1930 
Nov 4; San Antonio, Texas. USA: IEEE Computer Society Press; 1992: pp. 
46-54. ISBN: 0-8186-3115-5.
The US Air Force Air Mobility Command (AMC) World Wide Miltary 
Command and Control System (WWMCCS) Crisis Action Team (CAT) 
Guard (WCG) system provides a multilevel secure electronic interface 
between AMC's Top Secret System High Command and Control 
Information System and AMC's Secret System High CAT Global Decision 
Support System (GDSS). The WCG, implemented on HFSI's B3 XTS-200, 
can replace manual air-gap procedures. The WCG supports two-way data 
interchange for the automated release of sanitised High-to-Low Time 
Phased Force Deployment Data (TPFDD) Operation Plans (OPLAN) and 
Low-to-High Joint Operations Planning and Execution System (JOPES) 
update data, as well as operator mediated High-to-Low and automatic 
Low-to-High WWMCCS Interconnection Network (WIN) Teleconference 
(TLCF) message exchange.
	This paper summarizes the functional capabilities of the AMC 
WCG, citing its unique features and describing its current 
implementation status. A "guard" mediates and controls the flow of 
information between systems operating at different security levels.
/guard/US Air Force/Air mobility command/AMC.

