Wagner, N. R.; Putter, P. S.; Cain, M. R. Encrypted Database Design; 
Specialised Approaches. 1986 Apr. 
IEEE Comp. Soc. Proc. 1986 Symp. Security and Privacy pp.148-155
The paper presented two ways of using cryptographic techniques to 
allow a database to be held and processed at an insecure central site, 
with query initiation and interpretation being performed at a secure 
local workstation. The first method is suitable for keyword searches of 
a large, static text file (too large to be held by the workstation), and 
the second uses homophonic cyphers on a more general database 
allowing complex queries and joins.
/databases/crypto. 

