Weissman, Clark (Paramax Systems Corporation). BLACKER: Security for 
the DDN Examples of A1 Security Engineering Trades. in: 1992 IEEE 
Symposium on Research in Security and Privacy; 1992 May 4; Oakland, 
California. USA: IEEE Computer Society Press; 1992: pp. 286. 
It can be done! It is within the state of the art to build an Al secure 
system, and the technology is reduced to practice on the BLACKER 
Program, a security applique for providing host-to-host secure 
communications across the Defense Data Network, DDN. This report 
presents examples of successful technical accomplishments and 
identifies important factors which made progress possible on the 
BLACKER Program. Based on a presentation at the DCA workshop on 
Computer and Communications Security, McLean Va., July 1986, this 
paper was presented, but not published, at the IEEE Symposium on 
Security and Privacy, Oakland Ca., April 1988.
/networks.

