Wiseman, S. R. (RSRE). Abstract and Concrete Models for Secure 
Database Applications. in: Fifth IFIP WGI 1.3 Working Conference on 
Database Security; 1991 Nov; Shepherdstown, West Virginia. USA. 
Two data models are presented, one is abstract and is similar to the 
entity-relationship model, the other is more concrete and is similar to 
the relational model. The definition of the models is intended to clearly 
separate the abstract and concrete concerns which arise from 
designing a database application. Upon this firm foundation, a fine 
grained classification scheme is added and an overview of the mapping 
from the abstract to concrete model is provided.
databases/relational databases Models.

Wiseman, S. R. Audit Control in Databases. in: Procs. of the Seventh 
International IFIP TC'11 Conference on Information Security; May 15; 
Brighton, UK. ; 1991 May 15; SMITE Ref:  1012. 
Current DBMSs do not provide adequate support for applications which 
must maintain journals that are used for later auditing. Integrity 
constraints and triggers are examined and it is shown that they do not 
offer a complete solution. The idea of Trigger Groups, which allow 
triggered actions to take place in new transactions, is introduced as an 
extension to ordinary triggers and is shown to satisfy the journalling 
requirements.
