Wiseman, S. R. Basic Mechanisms for Computer Security
 1990 Jan 1. 
The protection facilities required for computer security are expressed 
as four basic mechanisms. It is shown how a security model maps to 
these mechanisms and how they can be implemented on conventional 
architectures, capability architectures and in high level languages.
