Wiseman, S. R. On the Problem of Security in Data Bases. in: Database 
Security III: Status and Prospects. 3rd IFIP WG 11.3 Working Conference 
on Database Security. 
This paper addresses the fundamental problems of providing multi-
level secure data base management systems. It is shown that the 
Inference problem arises because data is used as an addressing 
mechanism. Existing solutions are described, but these are shown to 
have unfortunate consequences for the data base user and so 
alternatives are suggested. The problems of Aggregation and Deductions 
from real world knowledge are also considered. Also: Database Security 
III: Status and Prospects. Third IFIP WG 11.3 Working Conference on 
Database Security, Monterey, California, USA September 1989.
