Wiseman, S. R. On the garbage collection of block structured memories. 
1985 Jan 3. 
A survey of existing garbage collection methods is presented. These are 
considered as candidates for use in a system where memory address 
space is shared by all users of a computer. The special problems that 
arise from this requirement are described and it is shown that no one 
garbage collector solves all the problems.
