Zajac, B. P. Computer Viruses.  Can They Be Prevented? Computer Law & 
Security Report. 1989 May; 5(4): 18.
Note: Abstract in TechGnosis, June 1989 (PO689-25).
A brief review of the history of computer viruses is illustrated with 
examples of a number of viruses and details of how they replicate 
themselves.  A checklist of methods of prevention and detection is 
given, together with advice about the actions that can be taken in the 
event of infection.  There is also a consideration of the possible 
avenues of legal action that might be open to an organisation that has 
suffered from a virus and that wishes to claim redress, but these 
appear to be limited in practice.
/security/viruses.

